00README — DINOv3 Head Selection (v28.4.2 camera-ready)

This is the arXiv auto-discovery README for the v28.4.2 camera-ready preprint of "DINOv3 Head Selection for Few-Shot Industrial Defect Detection: An Empirical Study" (Zhang, Xu, Wei). It accompanies the LaTeX source, compiled PDF, and bibliographic files in this submission bundle.

PAPER METADATA

Title: DINOv3 Head Selection for Few-Shot Industrial Defect Detection: An Empirical Study

Authors: Zhang Zhenyi (corresponding), Xu Xitao, Wei Ziqiang

Affiliation: NARI Nanjing Water Conservancy and Hydropower Technology Co., Ltd. (国电南瑞南京水利水电科技有限公司), Department of Digital Intelligence R&D, Nanjing, China

Contact: Z467718583@126.com

Venue: IEEE Transactions on Industrial Informatics (TII) — primary target; IEEE Transactions on Instrumentation and Measurement (TIM) — backup

Submission date: 2026-07-26

Version: v28.4.2 (camera-ready)

GitHub: https://github.com/467718584/dinov3-head-selection

ABSTRACT

We report the first systematic empirical study of DINOv3 (Meta AI Research, 2025) with four detection heads on four backbones across five shot levels and five random seeds, totaling 1,221 measured configurations on three public industrial defect benchmarks (NEU-DET steel surface, Crack500 pavement, full 15-category MVTec AD manufactured goods). We report three findings. First, reproducing DINOv3 from Meta-native `.pth` checkpoints via `timm` silently drops 51% of pretrained weights (Rotary Position Embeddings and 4 storage tokens are incompatible with timm's stock ViT loader); our `dinov3_native.py` loader restores 100% loading. Second, across the multi-head selection matrix, YOLOv11-seg dominates the frozen-DINOv3 linear-probe regime (NEU-DET 99.60% / MVTec AD 73.93% AUROC), with EoMT and AD-DINOv3 statistically indistinguishable after Holm-Bonferroni correction (Friedman p=0.0091). Third, we document a pre-submission retraction: an early claim that RegTTA (Register-Anchored Test-Time Recalibration) was "bit-identical to vanilla PatchCore" on a 200-image subset is replaced by a monotone AUROC degradation of 0.60-11.27 pp depending on regularization strength, on the full 1,725-image test set. This retraction follows the 4-Stage Honest Negative-Ablation Protocol formalized in our companion paper `paper3_TIPL v0.7 §3.4`. All code, the 25,372 `.pt` feature cache (15.8 GB), and the pre-registration artifacts are released under Apache 2.0.

