HONEST SCOPE DISCLOSURE

This preprint reports:
- 7-step-equivalent 1,221 configurations across NEU-DET, Crack500, MVTec AD
- 15.8 GB of pre-computed DINOv3 patch features (25,372 .pt files)
- 5-seed reproducibility on NEU-DET and Crack500 primary tables
- 4-Stage Honest Negative-Ablation Protocol application on PEMB + RegTTA
- 4 backbone × 4 head × 5 shots × 5 seeds = 400 NEU-DET configurations

This preprint does NOT report:
- Cross-device T4 / Jetson Orin deployment (planned v29)
- Crack500 4-backbone full matrix (ConvNeXt-T + ViT-L/16 deferred to v29)
- MVTec AD full multi-seed validation on all 405 cells (3 seeds only, std ≈30 pp)
- Multi-class joint training across NEU-DET 6 classes (only 60/20/20 split; per-class)

The 51% loading gap is not a benchmark figure but a reproducibility artifact; the actual downstream accuracy degradation depends on the head and dataset (22-60 pp across our measurements).

